The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Mahesh, Chawla shine with ball

 - U-19 Test vs Pakistan 

Rawalpindi: The Indian under-19 team led by an inspired performance from pacer V Yo Mahesh reduced Pakistan under-19 side to 63 for five and were on the verge of victory on Day III of the first junior Test match being played here at the Rawalpindi Cricket Stadium. 

Having set Pakistan a daunting victory target of 446 runs, Mahesh took three for 29 and skipper Piyush Chawla clipped in with two for 12 to leave the home side in tatters in just 26 overs. 

Pakistan require another 383 runs to win the first match of the two-game Test series. 

Only opener Ahmed Shahzad withstood the Indian attack, scoring a courageous 38 before being dismissed just before close. Behram Khan (1) and Imad Wasim (5) were at the crease at stumps. 

Earlier, on a good batting pitch, the Indians resumed their second essay at the overnight score of 42 without loss went on to make 303 for six in 74.1 overs before declaring their innings. 

India had taken a first innings lead of 142 runs after skittling out the hosts for just 147 on the Day II. 

On Saturday, opener Cheteshwar Pujara (85) and Uday Kaul (67) put on 107 runs for the second wicket. (PTI) 




